title: SFH on Hospital Authority Review Steering Committee (with photos)
content_text:
p>
			Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for 
			Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after inspecting the medical 
			services of United Christian Hospital this afternoon (August 21): Secretary for Food and Health: In the 2013 Policy Address, the Chief 
			Executive committed to conduct a review of the operation of the 
			Hospital Authority (HA). Earlier today, the Government announced the 
			setting up of a Steering Committee to carry out an overall review of

setting up of a Steering Committee to carry out an overall review of 
			HA. The objective of this review is to ensure that HA can meet up to 
			the challenge of ageing population as well as the changing public 
			needs for health-care services. The review will cover HA's 
			management and cluster arrangement, resource allocation, service 
			levels and its overall cost-effectiveness. I will be the chairperson 
			of the Steering Committee, which comprises 13 non-official members,

of the Steering Committee, which comprises 13 non-official members, 
			other official members and representatives from HA. The non-official 
			members come from different sectors of the community including 
			health-care professionals, academics and representatives from 
			business, welfare sectors, patient advocates and front-line staff of 
			HA. I believe with their experience in public services and 
			management and health-care services, (members of) the Steering 
			Committee would provide constructive views and recommendations to

Committee would provide constructive views and recommendations to help the Government and HA further improve and strengthen HA's management, transparency and service quality. (The full membership list of the Steering Committee is in the Annex.) Reporter: (On the review.) Secretary for Food and Health: Through various channels of feedback, we have repeatedly received opinion that the cluster operation and the arrangement within HA is certainly an area which should be looked at by the Steering Committee.
